parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission suddenly downshifts
the vehicle decelerates without warning
the traction control light comes on
and the gear display is blank.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
and the vehicle stalls or loses power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission solenoid can cause the transmission to malfunction, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission solenoid fails
causing the transmission to slip or hesitate
and the vehicle may stall or lose power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The headlight flickering and dimming can cause a distraction to the driver and oncoming traffic, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Headlights flicker or dim when applying brakes
slowing down
or releasing the accelerator pedal; headlights strobe or flash; exterior lights flicker or dim when brake or gas pedal is pressed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The electrical system failure can cause a loss of power to critical systems, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Instrument panel pops out of the display paneling; dashboard lights flash and go into limp mode; cruise control quits working; traction control light comes on; check engine light comes on; all electrical systems shut off for a split second.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The door sensor issue can cause a distraction to the driver and increase the risk of accidents due to the sudden and unexpected activation of interior lights.
symptoms: Interior lights turn on and the dash indicates that the rear passenger door is open when it is not; interior lights come on and the dash indicates the door is open when the doors automatically lock due to speed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The headlamp flickering/dimming during braking can cause reduced visibility, distraction, and increased risk of accidents, particularly at night or in low-light conditions.
symptoms: Headlights flicker or dim when braking
high beam lights blink or flash when braking
low beam lights dim when braking
instrument lights dim slightly when braking
pulsating or strobe-like effect on headlights when decelerating or braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Condensation in the headlamp housing can cause HID lights to fail, leading to reduced visibility and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Condensation buildup in headlamp housing
HID lights fail
foggy or cloudy headlamp lenses.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Headlamp aiming issues can cause reduced visibility, glare, and increased risk of accidents, particularly at night or in low-light conditions.
symptoms: Headlights are aimed too high
causing difficulty when driving at night
blind spots in the headlamp beam pattern.
